# GridMind — Power Grid Intelligence System

A production-grade multi-agent AI system that autonomously manages a national power grid. Built with **LangGraph**, **Gemini**, **Groq**, and a **Gymnasium RL environment**, GridMind coordinates four specialized AI agents to optimize plant output, monitor equipment health, and maximize transmission efficiency — all in real time.

---

## What It Does

GridMind runs a continuous decision loop across six power plants and six transmission lines spanning India's five demand zones. At each cycle:

1. A **Demand & Supply Agent** (Gemini LLM) analyzes regional forecasts, supply chain disruptions, raw material prices, and live weather to recommend per-plant output adjustments.
2. A **Plant Health Agent** (pure Python) reads live sensor data from SQLite — vibration, temperature, fault count, runtime hours — computes a composite health score, and auto-schedules maintenance.
3. A **Transmission Agent** (pure Python) evaluates line efficiency, calculates power loss per km, flags degraded lines, and recommends load-balancing shifts between zones.
4. A **Main Orchestrator** (Groq LLM) collects all three reports, resolves conflicts, computes the RL reward signal, and returns the next observation vector.

The entire pipeline is wrapped in a **Gymnasium-compatible RL environment** (`PowerGridEnv`) so it can be trained end-to-end with PPO or DQN via `stable-baselines3`.

---

## Architecture

```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│              Gymnasium RL Environment                   │
│         PowerGridEnv  (action: 0 / 1 / 2)              │
└────────────────────────┬────────────────────────────────┘
                         │  state + action
                         ▼
            ┌────────────────────────┐
            │   MAIN ORCHESTRATOR    │  ← Groq LLM
            │  conflict resolution   │
            │  reward · next state   │
            └──┬──────────┬──────────┘
               │          │          │
               ▼          ▼          ▼
        [Demand &    [Plant Health  [Transmission
         Supply]      Tracker]       Agent]
         Gemini LLM   Pure Python    Pure Python
               │          │          │
               └──────────┴──────────┘
                          │
                     SQLite Database
              (plant_health · transmission_lines
               maintenance_log · inspections)
```

**LangGraph** manages the directed graph execution. Each agent node runs sequentially: Demand → Health → Transmission → Orchestrator.

---

## Tech Stack

| Layer | Technology |
|---|---|
| Agent Framework | LangGraph + LangChain |
| LLM (Demand Agent) | Google Gemini 2.0 Flash |
| LLM (Orchestrator) | Groq — Llama 3.1 8B Instant |
| Real-time Search | Tavily API (weather impact) |
| RL Environment | Gymnasium (OpenAI Gym compatible) |
| Future RL Training | stable-baselines3 (PPO / DQN) |
| Backend API | FastAPI + Server-Sent Events |
| Database | SQLite (auto-seeded on startup) |
| Frontend | React 18 + Vite + Tailwind CSS |
| UI Libraries | Recharts · React-Leaflet · Framer Motion |

