## Agents & Tools

### Demand & Supply Agent (Gemini)
Analyzes demand vs. supply and recommends per-plant output changes.

| Tool | Description |
|---|---|
| `get_plant_capacity_tool` | Current output and max capacity per plant |
| `get_regional_demand_forecast_tool` | 24h demand forecast per zone |
| `get_supply_chain_status_tool` | Disruption index per fuel type |
| `get_raw_material_prices_tool` | Live prices for coal, gas, uranium, silicon |
| `get_distance_tool` | Transmission distance between plant and zone |
| `get_weather_impact_tool` | Real-time weather via Tavily → demand impact factor |

### Plant Health Agent (Pure Python)
Computes health scores and auto-schedules maintenance without any LLM calls.

| Tool | Description |
|---|---|
| `get_plant_runtime_tool` | Runtime hours, fault count, last maintenance |
| `get_plant_sensor_data_tool` | Vibration index, temperature, capacity % |
| `calculate_health_score_tool` | Composite 0–100 score + risk level |
| `schedule_maintenance_tool` | Writes to SQLite maintenance_log |
| `get_maintenance_schedule_tool` | All upcoming scheduled maintenances |
| `get_plants_needing_maintenance_tool` | Plants with score < 60 or urgent status |
| `get_all_plants_health_tool` | Full system health overview |

### Transmission Agent (Pure Python)
Evaluates line efficiency and recommends load shifts without any LLM calls.

| Tool | Description |
|---|---|
| `get_transmission_line_data_tool` | Full line record from database |
| `get_all_transmission_lines_tool` | All six lines at once |
| `calculate_transmission_loss_tool` | Power loss MW + efficiency score |
| `get_line_distance_consumption_ratio_tool` | MW/km ratio vs 0.8 benchmark |
| `recommend_load_balancing_tool` | Shift recommendations per demand zone |
| `flag_line_for_inspection_tool` | Writes flag to SQLite + updates status |
| `get_flagged_lines_tool` | All pending inspection flags |

### Main Orchestrator (Groq)
Resolves conflicts between agent recommendations and computes RL signals.

| Tool | Description |
|---|---|
| `get_system_summary_tool` | Full snapshot of all plants and lines |
| `resolve_conflicts_tool` | Applies policy rules to reconcile agent outputs |
| `compute_reward_tool` | Calculates scalar reward from database state |
| `compute_next_state_tool` | Returns normalized 6-float observation vector |

---

## Key Design Decisions

**Gemini key rotation** — The `GeminiKeyRotator` supports comma-separated keys in `GOOGLE_API_KEY` and automatically rotates on 429 rate-limit errors with per-key cooldown tracking. This keeps the demand agent running across long RL episodes.

**Groq for orchestrator** — The orchestrator uses a separate Groq quota so it never competes with the demand agent for Gemini rate limits.

**Zero-API health and transmission agents** — Both agents run as pure Python against SQLite, making them instant and free. Only the demand agent (needs real-time reasoning) and orchestrator (needs conflict resolution) use LLMs.

**Dynamic sensor perturbation** — Each RL `step()` applies small random noise to plant vibration, temperature, and capacity readings before running the pipeline, simulating real-world sensor drift.

---

## Database Schema

```sql
plant_health          -- 6 plants: sensor readings, runtime, fault count, maintenance status
maintenance_log       -- scheduled and completed maintenance events
transmission_lines    -- 6 lines: load, loss %, efficiency, status
transmission_inspections -- flagged lines pending inspection
```

The database is auto-created and seeded on first run via `setup_database()`.

